    <p>If you're like me and can't stand it when your friend's got the aux and he puts on modern country, give Bluegrass a try. I think it preserves the spirit of what Country originally was, while blending it with other genres like rock, jazz, and blues. But most importantly, it doesn't make me want to gouge my eardrums out with a pickaxe.</p>
